views.text: This deck contains flash cards from First Aid (BROS Deck), Pathoma (BROS Deck), USUHS lectures, and pictures from anatomy for your study.

{{c1::Marcus-Gunn Pupil}} is a pathological pupil that occurs due to optic nerve damage or a severe retinal injury and presents with a loss/decrease of bilateral pupillary constriction to light.

views.text: Many Cards are unclear about what you are supposed to be guessing as many of the photos have more than one point of emphasis.

Great work with detailed clinical relevance and enough coverage of all areas, but some false annotation on the image is confusing so need to be self-aware of them. Cadaveric images are sufficient but image quality is poor. Look forward to a better update, thanks. P.S I have completed over 75% of this deck, this is my sincere review.
